We recommended that the:
Treasurer (i) deposit/remit collections to the authorized depository bank intact daily; and 





(ii) ensure the correctness and reliability of entries in the Report of Collections and Deposits (RCDs) as supported by the accompanying official receipts and deposit slips;

b. Collecting Officers promptly render daily reports of collections and remit the full amount received and collected to the Treasury for deposit to the authorized depository bank;

c. ICO-Accountant (i) direct the concerned accounting personnel to perform thorough review of the correctness of entries and footings of the RCDs as reliable basis in the recording of collections and remittances of the Treasurer; and (ii) maintain separate subsidiary ledger for each collecting officer; and


d. AO concerned to prepare the RAAF monthly in accordance with the Manual on NGAS to be able to monitor and check regularly the inventory of used and unused accountable forms.

exert utmost effort to secure a copy of death certificate of the late Municipal Treasurer Vicente Viloria to warrant the request for write-off of his unliquidated cash advances totaling ₱795,335.80;


stop the practice of granting new cash advances without the liquidation of previous ones;

require the concerned personnel to liquidate their cash advances as soon as the purpose thereof had been accomplished; and



effect the necessary adjusting entry under the General Fund books to correct the erroneous debit of Training Expenses instead of Due from Officers and Employees for the cash advance granted under check no. 659760.

ICO-Municipal Accountant effect the necessary adjusting entries;

		ICO-Municipal Accountant, who maintains the GF books, coordinate with the accounting personnel in-charge in keeping the TF books in the recording of transactions affecting the two reciprocal accounts so as to ensure reconciliation of balances at all times;

Municipal Treasurer observe strictly the correct official receipts to be issued for each and every type of funds received in behalf of the Municipality; and

Management monitor strict compliance by those concerned to pertinent laws, rules and regulations.

Inventory and Appraisal Committee facilitate the completion of the physical count of all PPE items and provide a fully accomplished RPCPPE;

ICO – Municipal Accountant prepare and maintain property ledger cards and schedules for the PPE and exert efforts to secure the necessary documents and reports so that appropriate depreciation can be provided for the PPE accounts with no depreciation;

ICO – Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer strengthen the controls in the handling and recording procedures for the PPE by issuing ARE upon issuance of PPE to end-users and by performing a periodic reconciliation of the records of the accounting, property and actual inventory; and


ICO – Municipal Accountant effect the necessary adjusting entries to correct the deficiencies noted.

conduct a thorough review and analysis of all outstanding payables and liabilities;


review and monitor all booked obligations to ensure that only valid claims remain in the books; 



maintain and update regularly the subsidiary ledgers complete with the necessary details on the accounts; and


effect the necessary adjusting entries to: (1) cause the reversion to the unappropriated surplus of the Accounts Payables and Other Payables accounts which are undocumented and have been long outstanding for two years or more in compliance with Section 322 of R.A. No. 7160; and (2) transfer the balance of Philhealth Capitation to Due to GOCCs account.

scrutinize the details of the Due to Other NGAs account to determine the unreconciled difference of ₱222,355.04 between the amounts presented in subsidiary ledgers with the amount in the financial statements; 

properly comply with the MOA, issuances and pertinent COA rules and regulations on program implementation and reporting requirements of various fund transfers received;

see to it that all balances of PDAF funds which are not covered by Notice of Cash Allocations and Special Allotment Release Orders, whether obligated or not, be reverted to the Unappropriated Surplus of the General Fund; 

if the fund transfers are due for liquidation, prepare and submit liquidation reports for the expended portion and cause the return to the source agencies all unutilized balances of the fund transfers; and

improve the safekeeping of important documents especially MOAs for future references.

instruct the ICO – Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer to diligently remit in full all receipts owing to other LGUs and to make representations with the PGZ for the immediate reconciliation of the funds owing to the latter;

instruct the ICO – Municipal Accountant to review and verify correctness of journal entries arising from future events similar to the aforementioned transactions and take-up the following adjusting entries to correct the effects of erroneous entries on past transactions; and

